INTRODUCTION
The Idaho State Science Standards are essential for developing the science literacy of Idaho students, as it is vital that our students understand the
fundamental laws and practices within scientific disciplines. This document provides stakeholders with a set of rigorous and relevant science
performance standards that prepare students to be informed, contributing citizens of the 21st century world. The unifying goal is for Idaho
students to practice and perform science and use their working knowledge of science to successfully function in a complex world.
USING THIS DOCUMENT
Category Headings                                   Other Abbreviations                                  Science Domains
PS – Performance Standards                          ETS – Engineering and Technology Standard            LS – Life Science
SC – Supporting Content                             K – Kindergarten                                     PS – Physical Science
