 • Energy cannot be created or destroyed, but it can be transported from one place to another and transferred between systems. (PSP2-HS-1,
     PSP2-HS-4)
 • Mathematical expressions, which quantify how the stored energy in a system depends on its configuration (e.g. relative positions of charged
