  • Further Explanation: Emphasis is on how the experimental evidence supports the claim and how a theory is generally modified in light of new
     evidence. Examples of a phenomenon could include resonance, interference, diffraction, and photoelectric effect.
  • Content Limit: Assessment does not include using quantum theory.
PSP3-HS-4. Evaluate the validity and reliability of claims in published materials of the effects that different frequencies of electromagnetic
radiation have when absorbed by matter.
